HEADWORD: Farseeing
<hw>Far"see`ing</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Able
to see to a great distance; farsighted.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Having foresight as regards the future.</def>⟦br⟧
